@node "Intro" "Introduction to RPGEditor"
@{i}@{fg shine}Introduction to RPGEditor and RPGEngine@{ui}@{fg text}

You have got in your grubby little hands a copy of what I beleive to be the
best Role Playing Game creator for the Amiga (don't quote me on that).  It
has lots and lots of features and creates adventures small enough to hold
several on one floppy disk.  Here is a list of what it can do:

@{fg shine}  Both the Editor and Engine@{fg text}

    @{bg fill}* Have 32 colors available to all the graphics@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Use fast memory compression techniques to reduce file sizes@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}  (Pack and RLE)@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Have 256 Map Icons, and Maps up to 500x500 squares@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Have 256 Objects, with individual pictures and properties@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Have Customizable Object Messages with scripting!@{bg back}

@{fg shine}  The Editor@{fg text}

    @{bg fill}* Uses Click Tabs to organize the individual editors in a logical@{bg back}
      @{bg fill}(I sincerely hope!) fashion@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Has a neat Starfield Simulator screen saver@{bg back}

@{fg shine}  The Engine@{fg text}

    @{bg fill}* Has title, description, and exiting picture support@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Plays a Tracker MOD throughout the adventure@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Is very very speedy (always a good thing)@{bg back}
    @{bg fill}* Allows you, within object messages, to:@{bg back}

@{fg fill}      @{bg shine}# Play a CheeseAnim@{bg back}
      @{bg shine}# Show an IFF or SPACK image@{bg back}
      @{bg shine}# Read a text file@{bg back}
      @{bg shine}# Pause the output@{fg text}@{bg back}

